                <h1>Discover the Fascinating History of Groundhog Day</h1>
                <p>Groundhog Day, celebrated on February 2, has its roots in ancient European traditions. It arrived in the U.S. via German settlers in Pennsylvania, who believed a groundhog's prediction of spring weather could determine the season's arrival. Today, it features Punxsutawney Phil and a fun annual celebration.</p>
